## Feature Implementation Plans (`ai-specs/changes/`)

Each planned feature gets a file: `ai-specs/changes/<TICKET-ID>_<layer>.md`

### Template

```markdown
# <TICKET-ID>: <Feature Name>
**Layer**: backend | frontend | fullstack
**Status**: planned | in-progress | completed

## Context
Brief description of what this feature does and why.

## Architecture Impact
- What existing modules are affected
- New modules to be created
- Dependencies introduced

## Implementation Steps
1. [ ] Step description — expected outcome
2. [ ] Step description — expected outcome
...

## Test Specifications
### Unit tests
- [ ] Test: what it verifies
### Integration tests
- [ ] Test: what it verifies

## Definition of Done
- [ ] All tests pass (unit + integration)
- [ ] Pre-LLM pipeline passes (fmt + lint + types)
- [ ] Critic Pass completed
- [ ] ARCHITECTURE.md updated if decisions were made
- [ ] API spec updated if endpoints changed
- [ ] PR description references this plan
```
